Description: M-Lab node (autonode) measurement stack
 Native systemd packaging of the M-Lab "autonode" Network Diagnostic Tool
 (NDT) measurement platform, replacing the former Docker Compose deployment.
 .
 It runs ndt-server and its sidecar services - node registration, heartbeat,
 uuid-annotator, jostler, traceroute-caller (with scamper) and a Prometheus
 node exporter - as hardened systemd services confined with systemd's own
 sandboxing directives. No Docker is required at build or run time.
 .
 The component binaries are extracted from M-Lab's pinned container images at
 build time. The whole stack is controlled atomically through mlab-node.target.
